I've been using VSCode and I love it but I have some projects where I deal with twig tags and formatting code for TWIG templates is a nightmare..

Lets say for example I have:

```
{% for sushi in dinner.sushiArray %}
{% if sushi == 'New York' %}
<p>Yum</p>
{% else %}
<p>iew...</p>
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
```

This is what I get when formatting

```
 {% for sushi in dinner.sushiArray %} {% if sushi == 'New York' %}
<p>Yum</p>
{% else %}
<p>iew...</p>
{% endif %} {% endfor %} 
```

Is there a way to format correctly HTML in VSCode when we use Twig or Swig tags, like

`{% if ... %} {%else%} {%endif%} {% for %} {%endfor%} {% include %}, etc...`

For now code formatters remove all line breaks before and after those tags.

Was not able to find an suitable extension for that.. Neither a way to configure the internal code formatter.

Please, I need my sushi.
Thanks
